HEADWORD: Attar
<hw>At"tar</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per.
<ets>'atar</ets> perfume, essence, Ar. <ets>'itr</ets>, fr.
<ets>'atara</ets> to smell sweet. Cf. <er>Otto</er>.]</ety> <def>A
fragrant essential oil; esp., a volatile and highly fragrant essential
oil obtained from the petals of roses.</def> <altsp>[Also written
<asp>otto</asp> and <asp>ottar</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

